	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64264604"><p>
If you were expecting sediments (an accumulation of loose particles at the bottom of a body of water) to be impermeable or pinpoint the precise decade or century when certain events occurred, I applaud your optimism, I guess.
</p><p>
Words that <a href="https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/sciadv.adi8136" title="science.org">the paper</a> [science.org] uses to describe their findings do not include unusual, remarkable, unexpected, surprising/surprise, unanticipated, unforeseen, astonishing or even startling.
</p><p>
However, they note that "more elongated particles and fibers have reduced mobility" so yeah, maybe date the anthropocene using big immobile elongated particles rather than the microest of the microparticles.</p></div>
	</div>

